    'note.pointcloud':'<b>Note.</b> <strong>Communication Trajectory Cloud</strong> — 3D visualization of the N-period sender\u2013receiver game (Choi, Lee & Lim 2025; Sobel 2020).<br><strong>X-axis</strong>&thinsp;: Period (time). BT and GL games shown side-by-side, separated by a dashed divider. Each tick (BT.1, BT.2, \u2026 | GL.1, GL.2, \u2026) is one period of the repeated game.<br><strong>Y-axis</strong>&thinsp;: \u03bb (belief) — the receiver\u2019s posterior type belief, which <em>carries between periods</em> as inherited state. This is the core reputation variable: each period\u2019s \u03bb becomes the next period\u2019s prior.<br><strong>Z-axis</strong>&thinsp;: Receiver action (a<sub>t</sub>) — the behavioral response to the message, conditioned on the current belief.<br><strong>Markers</strong>&thinsp;: \u25cf circle = truth (m=\u03b8, Sobel Def. 3), \u25c6 diamond = lie (m\u2260\u03b8). Smaller markers indicate <em>deceptive</em> messages (Sobel Def. 4) — belief distortion independent of literal truth.<br><strong>Trajectory lines</strong>&thinsp;: semi-transparent lines connect the same agent across periods, making \u03bb-inheritance visible. Rising lines = reputation building; falling lines = trust erosion.<br><strong>Mean trajectories</strong>&thinsp;: bold blue (BT) and red (GL) lines show the population average \u03bb and action per period.<br><strong>Dotted floor line</strong>&thinsp;: prior belief \u03bb\u2080 = p<sub>b</sub>, the starting point before any communication.<br><strong>Color</strong>&thinsp;: by behavioral classification (V1) or AI model (V2). When N < 2, falls back to aggregate strategy\u2013welfare landscape.',
